SIMPLE: urbanity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Urbanity
<hw>Ur*ban"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>urbanitas</ets>; cf. F. <ets>urbanit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being urbane; civility or
courtesy of manners; politeness; refinement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The marquis did the honors of his house with the
<qex>urbanity</qex> of his country.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Polite wit; facetiousness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Raillery in the sauce of civil entertainment; and without some
such tincture of <qex>urbanity</qex>, good humor falters.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Politeness; suavity; affability;
courtesy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urbanize</ent>⟦br⟧
